<TITLE> AKM Atiqur Rahman new envoy to KL </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 09 (bdnews24.com)The government has appointed AKM Atiqur Rahman, currently serving as Bangladesh ambassador to Bhutan, as the next high commissioner to Malaysia, a foreign ministry statement said on Tuesday. A career diplomat Atiqur Rahman joined the Bangladesh Civil Service (Foreign Affairs) cadre in 1986, the statement said. Rahman served in Rome, Dakar and Hong Kong before becoming ambassador to Bhutan. He will replace Md Khairuzzaman who was recalled to the foreign ministry a few months back to face possible charges in the 'Jail Killings' case of 1975. Khairuzzaman, a former army major, has refused to come back and sought political asylum elsewhere, foreign ministry sources have said.
